WEBVTT

00:00:00.276 --> 00:00:02.916
There are things we accept
as obvious truths

00:00:02.916 --> 00:00:05.236
that aren't necessarily
backed up by data.

00:00:05.276 --> 00:00:06.556
For example,

00:00:06.556 --> 00:00:10.876
the idea that cousin marriage is,
to use a scientific term, icky.

00:00:10.876 --> 00:00:13.476
[Am I Normal? with Mona Chalabi]

00:00:13.476 --> 00:00:16.676
First off, cousin marriage
is way more common than you may think.

00:00:16.716 --> 00:00:19.036
Approximately 10 percent
of the world's families

00:00:19.076 --> 00:00:22.156
are headed by couples
who are second cousins or closer.

00:00:22.196 --> 00:00:25.316
That's more than 750 million people.

00:00:25.356 --> 00:00:28.716
And it maybe wildly out of fashion
in Europe and North America now,

00:00:28.716 --> 00:00:30.396
but like hoop skirts and top hats,